Excersises:

0) Write a program that prints all the arguments passed to it.
   	 -Loops,variables,printf

1) Write a program that opens a text-file. Print the contents of the file to the terminal.
   	 -fopen,string library

2) Write a program that reads a lower case input FILE. The program should then output an upper case version of the FILE.
   	 -fopen,string,ctype

3) Write a program that takes an arbitrary sized vector of numbers. Store the numbers in an array. The size of this array must be dynamically set; NOT KNOWN AT COMPILE TIME. 
  Example of program call: ./program 3 4 2  
  Example output: a[0]=3   a[1]=4    a[2]=2
   	 -malloc,pointers


Challenges:

0) Write a program that exists in multiple files. From your main(), you should make calls to other functions you have written.
1) Atoi converts 0-9 ASCII characters into int-type variables. Make a program, htoi, that includes hexadecimal digits: 0-F.